1️⃣ We are only working through the foot, ankle, and calf. Very little activity in the knees and hips.

2️⃣ We are now working through the entire lower body, flexing and extending at the ankles, knees, and hips.

Muscle Up 🧠⚡️

A muscle-up is a compound calisthenics exercise that combines a pull-up with a push. It begins with a hanging position, pulling the body up until the chest reaches the bar, and then transitioning into a push by pushing the body up until the arms are fully extended. This movement requires upper body strength, coordination, and core engagement. Advanced variations include the strict muscle-up, kipping muscle-up, and the rings muscle-up, each demanding different skill sets and muscle engagement. Mastering the muscle-up often involves progressive strength training and refining technique.

Quarter 1 goal is to be able to complete 10-15 consecutive reps! 🧠⚡️
